    • getLeafName

      public static String getLeafName(Model model, String nodeName, org.apache.commons.httpclient.URI uri, String method, String postData) throws HttpMalformedHeaderException
      Gets the name of the node to be used for the given parameters in the Site Map.
      Parameters:
      model - the model
      nodeName - the last element of the path
      uri - the full uri of the node, must not be null.
      method - the method for the node, must not be null.
      postData - the data of the request body.
      Returns:
      the name of the node to be used in the Site Map
      Throws:
      HttpMalformedHeaderException - if the uri is not correct.
      NullPointerException - if the uri or the method are null.
      Since:
      2.10.0

    • getRegexName

      public static String getRegexName(StructuralNode sn, boolean incParams)
      Returns a regex pattern that will match the specified StructuralNode, ignoring the parent and children. For most nodes this will just be the last element in the path, e.g. URL regex name https://www.example.com/aaa/bbb bbb https://www.example.com/aaa aaa https://www.example.com/ https://www.example.com Datadriven nodes are different, they will always return (.+?) to match anything.
      Parameters:
      sn - a StructuralNode
      incParams - if true then include URL params in the regex, otherwise exclude them
      Returns:
      a regex pattern that will match the specified StructuralNode, ignoring the parent and children.

    • getCleanRelativeName

      public static String getCleanRelativeName(StructuralNode sn, boolean incParams)
      Returns the name of the node ignoring the parent and children, i.e. the last element in the path. Data driven nodes will return the user specified name surrounded by the double angled brackets.
      Parameters:
      sn - a StructuralNode
      incParams - if true then include URL params in the regex, otherwise exclude them
      Returns:
      the name of the node ignoring the parent and children
